===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|holi|lang=enm}}, {{term|hali|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hāliġ}}, {{m|ang|hāleġ||holy, consecrated, sacred, venerated, godly, saintly, ecclesiastical, pacific, tame}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hailagaz||holy, bringing health}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hailaz||healthy, whole}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*kóh₂ilus||healthy, whole}}, equivalent to {{suffix|whole|y|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|haly||holy|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|hillich||holy|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|hillig||holy|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|heilig||holy|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|heilig||holy|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|hellig||holy|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|helig||holy|lang=sv}}. More at {{l|en|whole}}.

